PLEASE CONSULT CURRENT UCSD GENERAL CATALOG FOR ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION. </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Special Advising Note: </strong></p><p><strong>Transfer students are strongly advised to complete as many preparatory courses for their major before enrolling at UC San Diego. Preparing well for the major helps students move efficiently toward graduation. </strong></p><p><br></p><p>For information about the Department of Literature, including checklists of lower-division and upper-division requirements for all of our majors, descriptions of current courses and current class schedules, please go to: <a href=\"http://literature.ucsd.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://literature.ucsd.edu/</a> </p><p><br></p><p>Students electing the Literature/Writing major should be aware that it has a dual focus in 1) the study of literature and literary analysis and 2) the study of writing as a craft. </p><p><br></p><p>As with all of the literature majors offered at UCSD, there is a secondary language and literature requirement (see choices of languages below). This entails required study in a language other than English and the attainment of proficiency in that language through the terminal course in that particular language sequence. For details on the secondary language & literature requirement, please go to: <a href=\"http://literature.ucsd.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://literature.ucsd.edu</a><a href=\"http://literature.ucsd.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">/</a>. Students can prepare for this requirement by taking lower-division courses (enough to reach fluency level, usually one to two years) in American Sign Language, French, German, Greek, Hebrew, Italian, Korean, Latin, Russian, or Spanish. </p><p><br></p><p><strong>Literature/Writing majors are required to complete: </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>1) LTEN 26 </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>2) Any two of the following: </strong></p><p class=\"ql-indent-1\"><strong>LTEN 21, 22, 23, 25, 27, 28, 29 </strong></p><p class=\"ql-indent-1\"><strong>GSS 21, 22, 23, 25, 26. </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>3) LTWR 8A, 8B, and 8C (most often these courses are taken at UCSD). </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>4) The secondary language and literature requirement in the chosen language. </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>See appropriate lower-division articulated community college courses below.</strong></p>","groupId":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","position":1,"area":"General"}]
